@startuml
title Fortuna - Local Runtime / Deployment Diagram

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

node "Developer machine" {
  node "Browser" {
    [Fortuna Frontend\nReact SPA] as Frontend
  }

  node "Vite dev server\nhttp://localhost:5173" {
    [Static assets\nJS/CSS/images] as Vite
  }

  node "ASP.NET Core process\nFortuna.Api" {
    [Controllers] as Controllers
    [Application handlers] as Handlers
    [Domain model] as Domain
    [EF Core WriteDbContext] as WriteContext
    [EF Core ReadDbContext] as ReadContext
    [OutboxMessageProcessor] as OutboxProcessor
    [Swagger UI] as Swagger
  }

  node "SQL Server\nlocalhost" {
    database "FortunaWriteDb" as WriteDb
    database "FortunaReadDb" as ReadDb
  }

  node "Bruno / API client" {
    [Manual API requests] as Bruno
  }
}

Frontend --> Vite : load app bundle
Frontend --> Controllers : REST JSON API\nCORS allowed origin
Bruno --> Controllers : REST JSON API
Controllers --> Handlers : commands / queries
Handlers --> Domain : business rules
Handlers --> WriteContext : transactional writes
Handlers --> ReadContext : dashboard reads
WriteContext --> WriteDb : Customers, Products,\nTransfers, Transactions,\nOutboxMessages
ReadContext --> ReadDb : ProductTile,\nTimelineEvent,\nProcessedOutboxMessage
OutboxProcessor --> WriteDb : read unprocessed outbox
OutboxProcessor --> ReadDb : update projections
Swagger --> Controllers : test endpoints

note bottom of Controllers
  JWT Bearer authentication
  protects dashboard, accounts
  and transfer endpoints.
end note

@enduml
